{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id521f311a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"§ 5.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Salaries of justices","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Chief Justice and each associate justice shall each receive a salary at annual rates determined under section 225 of the Federal Salary Act of 1967 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s351–361"},"text":"2 U.S.C. 351–361","children":[],"tail":"), as adjusted by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s461"},"text":"section 461 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id521f311b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/870"},"text":"62 Stat. 870","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-03-02/ch9/s1/a"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1955, ch. 9, § 1(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/9"},"text":"69 Stat. 9","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426/tIV/s403/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–426, title IV, § 403(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-14"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/434"},"text":"78 Stat. 434","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/82/tII/s205/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–82, title II, § 205(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/422"},"text":"89 Stat. 422","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id521f311c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id521f311d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 324 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s218"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 218","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1152"},"text":"36 Stat. 1152","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1926-12-13/ch6/s1"},"text":"Dec. 13, 1926, ch. 6, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/919"},"text":"44 Stat. 919","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-07-31/ch704/s1"},"text":"July 31, 1946, ch. 704, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/716"},"text":"60 Stat. 716","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The provision “to be paid monthly” was omitted since the time of payment of salaries is a matter of administrative convenience. (See 20 Comp. Gen. 834.)","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Minor changes in phraseology were made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id521f311e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id521f311f-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 225 of the Federal Salary Act of 1967, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/206/s225"},"text":"section 225 of Pub. L. 90–206","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/642"},"text":"81 Stat. 642","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to chapter 11 (§ 351 et seq.) of Title 2, The Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id521f3120-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1975—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/82"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–82","children":[],"tail":" substituted provisions setting the annual salary of the Chief Justice and each associate justice at rates determined under section 225 of the Federal Salary Act of 1967, as adjusted by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s461"},"text":"section 461 of this title","children":[],"tail":", for provisions granting the Chief Justice and each associate justice a salary of $40,000 and $39,500 a year, respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1964—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–426","children":[],"tail":" increased salary of Chief Justice from $35,500 to $40,000 and that of Associate Justices from $35,000 to $39,500."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1955—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-03-02"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1955","children":[],"tail":", increased salary of Chief Justice from $25,500 to $35,500 and salaries of Associate Justices from $25,000 to $35,000 a year."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id521f3121-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id521f3122-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1964 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–426","children":[],"tail":" effective on first day of first pay period which begins on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1964","children":[],"tail":", except to extent provided in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426/s501/c"},"text":"section 501(c) of Pub. L. 88–426","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426/s501"},"text":"section 501 of Pub. L. 88–426","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id521f3123-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1955 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-03-02"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1955","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-03-01"},"text":"Mar. 1, 1955","children":[],"tail":", see section 5 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-03-02"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1955","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s4501"},"text":"section 4501 of Title 2","children":[],"tail":", The Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id521f3124-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id521f3125-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Salary Increases","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For adjustment of salaries of Chief Justice and Associate Justices under this section, see the executive order detailing the adjustment of certain rates of pay set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5332"},"text":"section 5332 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For prior year salary increases per the recommendation of the President, see Prior Salary Recommendations notes under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s358"},"text":"section 358 of Title 2","children":[],"tail":", The Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For miscellaneous provisions dealing with adjustments of pay and limitations on use of funds to pay salaries in prior years, see notes under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5318"},"text":"section 5318 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Salary of Chief Justice increased from $20,500 to $25,500 a year, and salaries of associate justices increased from $20,000 to $25,000 a year, by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-07-31/ch704/s1"},"text":"act July 31, 1946, ch. 704, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/716"},"text":"60 Stat. 716","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Salary of Chief Justice increased from $15,000 to $20,500 a year, and salaries of associate justices increased from $14,500 to $20,000 a year, by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1926-12-13/ch6/s1"},"text":"act Dec. 13, 1926, ch. 6, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/919"},"text":"44 Stat. 919","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Salary of Chief Justice set at $15,000 a year and salaries of associate justices set at $14,500 a year by Judicial Code of 1911, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s1"},"text":"act Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1152"},"text":"36 Stat. 1152","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
